HOUSE BILL 1231
F3 6lr2118
By: Delegates Wivell, Baker, and Valentine
Introduced and read first time: February 11, 2026
Assigned to: Ways and Means and Appropriations
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Washington County – Dually Enrolled Students
3 FOR the purpose of altering the definition of “dually enrolled student” to include both a
4 nonpublic secondary school student and a homeschool student in Washington County
5 so that these students are eligible to apply for the Part–Time Grant Program and
6 the Early College Access Grant; altering the definition of “full–time equivalent
7 enrollment” to include both a nonpublic secondary school student and a home school
8 student in Washington County; and generally relating to institutions of higher
9 education and dually enrolled students.
10 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
11 Article – Education
12 Section 5–201(a) and (e)
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
15 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
16 Article – Education
17 Section 5–201(g)
18 Annotated Code of Maryland
19 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
20 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
21 Article – Education
22 Section 15–127, 18–1401, and 18–14A–01
23 Annotated Code of Maryland
24 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
25 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
26 Article – Education
27 Section 18–14A–02 and 18–14A–03
